Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Andrias. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roan Museum, ABC 049.14.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (27)
